  <!-- Review Number 1 -->
<div class="w3-container w3-padding-32 w3-center">  
  <h3 id="Review1">Lily's Ice Cream Parlor</h3>
  <img src="/Users/Admin-PC/Desktop/ice cream.jpg" alt="Food" style="width:50%">
        <p>My first time visiting Lily’s Ice Cream Parlor, I was taken aback by the beautiful decor in the shop. It is flower themed, and it was the most plants I’d ever seen in a room! Simply breathtaking, this place is worth visiting for the photo opps alone! Although small, it is very homely and cozy. I ordered the signature Pecan Tart ice cream in their homemade waffle cones, and it was delicious! Creamy and decadent, you could tell it was fresh. I also got the Pistachio-Rose ice cream, this time in a cup. It had a unique flavour, unlike anything I’d eaten in the past. It had perhaps drawn inspiration from the east, as it tasted similar to eastern desserts I have eaten in the past. It was great ice cream and a great experience. I’ll definitely be back with some of my girlfriends!</p>
      </p>
